

```json
{
  // AI Readiness Scanner — VS Code Extension Debug Profiles
  //
  // Prerequisites:
  //   npm run compile   (or let the preLaunchTask handle it)
  //
  // Profiles:
  //   1. "Run Extension"        — launches a new Extension Host window with the extension loaded
  //   2. "Extension Tests"      — runs Vitest-based tests inside the Extension Host
  //
  // Usage:
  //   Press F5 or open the Run and Debug panel (Ctrl+Shift+D) and select a profile.
  //   The "npm: watch" preLaunchTask compiles src/ in watch mode so changes reload automatically.
  //
  // Troubleshooting:
  //   - If the Extension Host doesn't start, ensure `npm run compile` succeeds first.
  //   - Check the Debug Console for activation errors from src/extension.ts.
  //   - Confirm package.json `main` points to the correct bundled output.
  //
  // Related files:
  //   .vscode/tasks.json                — defines the "npm: watch" and "npm: compile" build tasks
  //   esbuild.js                        — bundles the extension for distribution
  //   src/extension.ts                  — extension entry point (activate / deactivate)
  //   vitest.config.ts                  — test runner configuration
  //   docs/AGENTIC_CODING_ASSESSMENT_SPEC.md — scoring spec the scanner implements

  "version": "0.2.0",
  "configurations": [
    {
      // Launches a sandboxed VS Code window (Extension Host) with the
      // AI Readiness Scanner extension loaded from the local build output.
      // Open a workspace folder in that window and run the
      // "AI Readiness Scanner: Scan Workspace" command to test scanning.
      "name": "Run Extension",
      "type": "extensionHost",
      "request": "launch",
      "args": [
        "--extensionDevelopmentPath=${workspaceFolder}"
      ],
      "outFiles": [
        "${workspaceFolder}/dist/**/*.js"
      ],
      "preLaunchTask": "npm: watch"
    },
    {
      // Runs the extension's test suite inside the Extension Host.
      // Tests are discovered by vitest.config.ts.
      // Results appear in the Debug Console.
      "name": "Extension Tests",
      "type": "extensionHost",
      "request": "launch",
      "args": [
        "--extensionDevelopmentPath=${workspaceFolder}",
        "--extensionTestsPath=${workspaceFolder}/out/test"
      ],
      "outFiles": [
        "${workspaceFolder}/dist/**/*.js"
      ],
      "preLaunchTask": "npm: watch"
    }
  ]
}
```